what works:
    - checkpointing a program with ./ckpt <executable>
    - reading a checkpoint image file (always named ckpt.dat)
      with ./readckpt ckpt.dat
    - restarting from a checkpoint image file with ./restart ckpt.dat

makefile usage:
    - make build: builds all executables as well as libckpt.so
    - make clean: removes all executables, libckpt.so and ckpt.dat
    - make check-count: checkpoints and restarts the count program
    - make check-matrix: checkpoints and restarts the matrix program

note:
    - make check-count and check-matrix only checkpoint and restart once;
      to test multiple restarts (which should work) you can repeatedly
      use ./restart ckpt.dat
